data.title: Application changes when you enable Management Center
data.meta_description: Enabling Management Center changes a number of files.
data.text:
Enabling Management Center changes a number of files.

When you enable Management Center:

If you did not already have foundation enabled, all the application changes associated with enabling foundation occur.

Changes are made to the WebSphere Commerce EAR file.

No changes are made to the database. Enabling Management Center does not create new tables, alter existing tables, create new indexes, create new triggers, or create new keys.

Changes to the EAR file when Management Center is enabled

The following changes occur:

Files are deleted from the WebSphere Commerce EAR file

Files are added to the WebSphere Commerce EAR file

Files are changed in the WebSphere Commerce EAR file

Files deleted from the WebSphere Commerce EAR file

The following files are deleted from the WebSphere Commerce EAR file:
